<text>Witt is a city in Montgomery County, Illinois, United States. The population was 785 at the 2020 census, down from 903 in 2010.

==Geography==
Witt is in eastern Montgomery County along Illinois Route 16, which leads southwest to Hillsboro, the county seat, and northeast to Nokomis.

According to the U.S. Census Bureau, Witt has a total area of , all land.

==Demographics==

As of the census of 2000, there were 991 people, 438 households, and 261 families residing in the city. The population density was . There were 480 housing units at an average density of .

